Here are the findings from the audit. I reviewed all 44 changed files against the CLAUDE.md rules.

---

**Finding 1: if/else chain on discriminated union `.type` field — ts-pattern not used**

File: `apps/web/src/features/auth/ui/PairGatePage.tsx`, lines 64–70

The `pairViaRelay` function dispatches on `msg.type` using if/else:

```ts
if (msg.type === "pair_success" && msg.token) {
  resolve({ token: msg.token });
} else if (msg.type === "pair_failed") {
  reject(new Error(msg.message || "Pairing failed"));
} else {
  reject(new Error("Unexpected response from relay"));
}
```

CLAUDE.md rule violated: *"Use `ts-pattern` for switch/case and if/else chains on discriminated unions. Prefer `.exhaustive()` to catch missing cases at compile time."* and *"When to use: Any switch/case or if/else chain dispatching on `.type`, `.status`, `.state`, or similar discriminator fields."*

This is an if/else chain dispatching on `.type` — exactly the pattern CLAUDE.md says to replace with `match(msg).with("pair_success", ...).with("pair_failed", ...).otherwise(...)`.

---

**Finding 2: Duplicate `createBoundaryErrorHandler` — private copy in DesktopShell instead of importing the shared export**

File: `apps/web/src/app/shells/DesktopShell.tsx`, lines 29–39

`DesktopShell.tsx` defines its own private `createBoundaryErrorHandler` function that is byte-for-byte identical to the `export function createBoundaryErrorHandler` that was simultaneously extracted to `apps/web/src/shared/utils/errorReporting.ts` in this same PR (line 66). `App.tsx`, `settings.tsx`, and `workspace.tsx` all correctly import from `errorReporting.ts`; `DesktopShell.tsx` alone does not.

CLAUDE.md rule violated: *"ALWAYS prefer editing an existing file to creating a new one"* / *"Split functionality into reusable components. Follow single responsibility principle."* The shared utility was explicitly created to avoid this duplication and `DesktopShell.tsx` should import from it like every other consumer does.

---

**No violations found for:**
- WebSocket push over polling: All subscribable `QUERY_RESOURCES` (`workspaces`, `stats`, `sessions`, `session`, `messages`) are properly subscribed via `useQuerySubscription` with `staleTime: Infinity` and `refetchOnWindowFocus: false`. The `sendRequest` calls for these same resources are used only as `queryFn` fallbacks for initial load before WS connects — this is the documented and correct pattern.
- Polling discipline: `diffStats`/`diffFiles` still poll at 5s only when `sessionStatus === "working"` — explicitly permitted by CLAUDE.md.
- Zustand selector discipline: All new Zustand usages (`useUIStore((s) => s.openSettings)`, `useWorkspaceStore((s) => s.selectWorkspace)`) use individual selectors.
- Feature query hook location: All modified service files remain in `src/features/{feature}/api/{feature}.service.ts`. The route/shell files use existing feature hooks (`useSettings`, `useAuth`) not inline queries.
- No new `.md` documentation files were added.
- The `query-protocol-client.ts` changes use `match(type).with(...)` correctly for all new relay frame types.
- No unbounded lists were added without virtualization.

